<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PrimarySourceReference/262> rdfs:label "Primary Source Reference: #262" ;
	a dprr:PrimarySourceReference ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Cic. Att. VII 7.6" ;
	dprr:hasID 262 ;
	dprr:forAssertion <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertion/258> .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/7687> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #7687" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Cos. 458. See MRR 1.39. J. Suolahti suggests Fabius, Furius, Iulius, and Manlius as shorter nomina possible with this cognomen but considers Furius the most probable (Arctos 3, 1962, 215-228).\n" ;
	dprr:hasID 7687 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/212> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #212" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Fast. Cap.; cf. Chr. 354 (Carbeto); Fast. Hyd. (Atratino), so also Chr. Pasc.; and the cognomen {Gr} with the name of Minucius in Diod. Died in office (Fast. Cap., Degrassi 24f., 92, 362f.)." ;
	dprr:hasID 212 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/211> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #211" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "The cognomen Atratinus in Fast. Hyd. and Chr. Pasc. might suggest that in Fast. Cap. Carvetus (?) had the nomen Sempronius. This however is exceedingly dubious since on the stone a considerable space is left between the filiation and the part of the cognomen preserved, and there is room only for a name of six or seven letters (Degrassi 24f.). The cognomen does not reappear in the Fasti. For previous discussions, see Degrassi 92." ;
	dprr:hasID 211 .
